                <p id="p18"><b>Accessibility and navigating this website</b></p>
                <p>LateRooms.com takes our responsibility for making accessible web content and software seriously. LateRooms.com is committed to developing software products that promote accessibility for people with disabilities and meet current accessibility standards, including those defined by Section 508 website of the U.S. Rehabilitation Act and the W3C's Web Content Accessibility Guidelines. </p>
                <p>LateRooms.com is actively engaged in the ongoing process of testing our products and website for compliance with current accessibility standards 1.  </p>
                <p>At LateRooms.com we are working hard to provide access to services and information that are helpful to all our customers. Many Internet users with disabilities find web sites difficult to use simply because of the way they are designed. This website has been designed to be as accessible as possible and to be compatible with the types of adaptive technology used by people with disabilities, including screen readers. </p>
                <p>On this website you can control the size of the text, the colours and the stylesheets, dependant upon the functionality of your browser. </p>
                <p>To navigate through this website once you have gone beyond the homepage, please use the menu at the top of each page. </p>
                <p><a href="#top">Back to the top</a></p>
                <p id="p19"><b>Font sizes and stylesheets</b></p>
                <p>You may change the font size of this document to your preference through your browser by doing the following:-  </p>
                <ol class="alpha">
                    <li>In Internet Explorer, select View, then Text Size, and then your preferred size; or</li>
                    <li>If you are using an alternative browser, please refer to the specific browser instructions.</li>
                </ol>
                <p>You may import your own stylesheet into this website by doing the following:-. </p>
                <ol class="alpha">
                    <li>In Internet Explorer select tools, then Internet Options, and then accessibility. Next click on any or all of three checkboxes to ignore colours, font styles or font sizes. In the same window you can change your stylesheet by clicking the checkbox that says, 'format document using my stylesheet' then simply browse to your stylesheet and click ok;</li>
                    <li>In Netscape select Edit, then Preferences, and then Appearance. You will then be given the choice to specify your own colours and fonts; or</li>
                    <li>If you are using an alternative browser, please refer to the specific browser instructions.</li>
                </ol>
